<%= render "pages/public_nav" %>

<div class="pt-28 pb-24 px-6">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900">HIPAA Compliance</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: June 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Our Commitment</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Schedulite is designed from the ground up to handle Protected Health Information (PHI) responsibly. While we are a technology platform and not a covered entity, we treat all patient data as if it were PHI and implement controls accordingly.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Encryption</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 px-5 py-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">At Rest</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Patient name, phone, date of birth, email, and appointment notes are encrypted using AES-256 via Lockbox. Raw database access reveals only ciphertext. Encryption keys are stored separately from encrypted data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 px-5 py-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">In Transit</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">All connections use TLS 1.2+. HSTS headers are enforced. Session cookies are marked secure and httponly. No PHI is ever transmitted over unencrypted channels.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">SMS Safety</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">SMS messages sent to patients contain only:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-4">
          <% ["First name", "Appointment time", "Status updates", "Status page URL"].each do |item| %>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-teal-500 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5" /></svg>
              <span class="text-sm text-gray-600"><%= item %></span>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">We <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">never</span> include in SMS:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
          <% ["Last name", "Date of birth", "Diagnosis", "Reason for visit", "Insurance info", "Provider specialty"].each do |item| %>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
              <span class="text-sm text-gray-600"><%= item %></span>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">This is enforced by a boot-time template linter that prevents deployment of any SMS template containing prohibited fields. It cannot be overridden.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Access Controls</h2>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <% ["Four role levels (Owner, Manager, Provider, Staff) — each with specific, enforced permissions", "Sessions expire after 15 minutes of inactivity", "Multi-tenant architecture with row-level data isolation", "Cross-tenant access returns 404 (not 403) to prevent enumeration", "Login attempts tracked with IP address and user agent", "Brute force protection with auto-ban after 20 failed attempts"].each do |item| %>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 py-1">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-teal-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5" /></svg>
              <span class="text-sm text-gray-600"><%= item %></span>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Audit Logging</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Every read and write to Patient and Appointment records is logged with the user who made the change, a timestamp, and the old/new values. Audit logs are immutable — they cannot be modified or deleted by any user, including account owners.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Business Associate Agreement</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">We offer a BAA on our Pro and Enterprise plans. The application displays a reminder banner until a signed BAA is uploaded by the practice. Contact <a href="mailto:hello@schedulite.io" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-500 underline">hello@schedulite.io</a> to initiate the BAA process.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Third-Party Sub-processors</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 px-5 py-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Twilio</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">SMS delivery. Twilio offers a BAA on paid plans. Our SMS content never contains clinical PHI — only first names, appointment times, and status updates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 px-5 py-4">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Stripe</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Payment processing. Stripe does not sign BAAs — our payment flows send only tokens and dollar amounts, never PHI. Card data is handled entirely by Stripe (PCI-DSS Level 1).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
